thread.title: Between desert and ocean

title: Between desert and ocean
text:
Only registered TrekEarth members may write critiques. Photographer's Note 
 Arica - Between desert and ocean  In the north of Chile the desert touches the ocean. The few cities are clamped between both. This picture is taken in Arica on top of the Morro de Arica , a steep hill with a height of 139 meters above sea level. All along the Chilean coast undersea earthquakes and tsunamis occur. At the time of writing Chile had 9 earthquakes in the past 24 hours, 47 in the past 7 days, 315 in the past month and 588 in the past year. See http://earthquaketrack.com/p/chile/recent Last Wednesday an 8.3-magnitude earthquake struck off Chile's coast, with a startup of the tsunami alert and with coastal evacuations. At least three people were killed.
